ple attribute in your subclasses.\n\nIf using a custom node class, it should accept the following:\n    - a render method (`self.render`)\n    - a takes_context boolean\n    - a list (`args`)\n    - a dict (`kwargs`)\n    - a template name or `None`"]}, {"name": "yak.tags.TemplateTag.takes_context", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Whether or not this TemplateTag takes the template context.\n\nThis is deduced by inspecting the `render` method and looking at the name of its first arg."]}, {"name": "yak.tags.TemplateTag._arg_spec", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Cached property storing the argspec of the `render` method"]}, {"name": "yak.tags.TemplateTag.get_arg_spec", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "discard_self", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "yak.tags.TemplateTag.uuid", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "yak.tags.TemplateTag.clean_bits", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bits", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Called during tag parsing to extract the \"bits\"\n(raw pieces of the template string inside `{%` `%}`)\n\nThis method **modifies** `bits`"]}, {"name": "yak.tags.TemplateTag.clean_as", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bits", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Removes `as` keyword if present and store the `target_var` on the `TemplateTag`"]}, {"name": "yak.tags.TemplateTag.clean_with", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null